claim.claim-text:
1. A process for reducing endometriosis implants in a woman, having a peritoneal cavity and an uterine cavity, to reduce dysmenorrhoea in the woman relative to the woman's present dysmenorrhoea, comprising: 
mixing a compound which acts as a local anesthetic with a physiological salt to form a pharmaceutical composition comprising a pharmaceutically effective concentration of the local anesthetic with a pharmaceutically acceptable excipient; 
placing the pharmaceutical composition in a catheter; 
administering the pharmaceutical composition into the uterine cavity of the woman with the catheter; and 
pertubating the composition into the peritoneal cavity using the catheter and in an amount of the composition sufficient for reducing an activity level of the endometriosis implants to reduce the woman's dysmenorrhoea.
